That's us who were beating up
the communists.

00:41:01.070 --> 00:41:02.480
We are so proud."
 

00:41:02.480 --> 00:41:04.429
It's a very good book.
 

00:41:04.429 --> 00:41:09.380
There's another good book by
Rudy Koshar, a friend of mine at

00:41:09.380 --> 00:41:12.268
Wisconsin on the town of
Marburg.

00:41:12.268 --> 00:41:15.059
What they do is they get Nazis
into every voluntary

00:41:15.059 --> 00:41:17.849
association, basically,
and they take them over.

00:41:17.849 --> 00:41:21.092
What you have is the
atomization of society,

00:41:21.092 --> 00:41:25.389
what Ian Kershaw calls
"going to the Fuhrer."

00:41:25.389 --> 00:41:28.469
The only thing left is the
family.

00:41:28.469 --> 00:41:31.699
You protect yourself and the
family, or you thrive in the

00:41:31.699 --> 00:41:33.719
family, but you're in the
family.

00:41:33.719 --> 00:41:37.050
Your children are in Hitler
youth.

00:41:37.050 --> 00:41:43.090
There is no possible organized
way of opposition.

00:41:43.090 --> 00:41:44.920
Soccer clubs,
football clubs,

00:41:44.920 --> 00:41:48.449
everything is part of the
atomization because it's been

00:41:48.449 --> 00:41:50.280
taken over by the Nazis.
 

00:41:50.280 --> 00:41:52.949
There is almost no resistance
in Germany.

00:41:52.949 --> 00:41:54.610
I'll talk a little bit about
this next time.

00:41:54.610 --> 00:41:57.789
This was a regime that is
capable,

00:41:57.789 --> 00:42:00.692
as they did in Dusseldorf,
of hanging sixteen-year-old

00:42:00.692 --> 00:42:03.489
boys because they listened to
Benny Goodman,

00:42:03.489 --> 00:42:04.920
or were considered to be
slackers,

00:42:04.920 --> 00:42:06.000
or "work shy."
 

00:42:06.000 --> 00:42:07.920
There's that phrase again.
 

00:42:07.920 --> 00:42:14.335
This atomization of German
society makes all of this

00:42:14.335 --> 00:42:15.719
possible.
 

00:42:15.719 --> 00:42:18.489
When Stauffenberg places his
bomb,

00:42:18.489 --> 00:42:20.500
and the thing blows up and it
doesn't kill Hitler,

00:42:20.500 --> 00:42:23.086
Hitler amused himself and his
friends by--all of the people

00:42:23.086 --> 00:42:25.139
and all of the families of
people involved,

00:42:25.139 --> 00:42:29.409
they filmed them being slowly
strangled with wire.

00:42:29.409 --> 00:42:31.860
They laughed as they watched
the film.

00:42:31.860 --> 00:42:34.599
The most chilling thing,
even more than that,

00:42:34.599 --> 00:42:37.737
is that Germans pour into the
street in thirty or forty

00:42:37.737 --> 00:42:40.545
different cities,
as bombs have been raining down

00:42:40.545 --> 00:42:41.289
all the time.
 

00:42:41.289 --> 00:42:42.829
They thank God.
 

00:42:42.829 --> 00:42:44.969
Mein Gott,
you saved our Fuhrer!

00:42:44.969 --> 00:42:49.159
That's extraordinarily
difficult to explain.

00:42:49.159 --> 00:42:52.735
By 1944, the armies are full of
old men and boys,

00:42:52.735 --> 00:42:55.940
because basically everybody
else is dead.

00:42:55.940 --> 00:42:58.460
They keep fighting.
 

00:42:58.460 --> 00:43:02.820
They fight with astonishing,
foolish courage,

00:43:02.820 --> 00:43:05.099
until the bitter end.
 

00:43:05.099 --> 00:43:08.487
They believed,
not everybody believed,

00:43:08.487 --> 00:43:10.869
there will be a revival.
 

00:43:10.869 --> 00:43:15.612
Even the German Federal
Republic was just replete with

00:43:15.612 --> 00:43:21.070
very proud former Nazis who take
hugely important positions in

00:43:21.070 --> 00:43:22.949
power after that.
 

00:43:22.949 --> 00:43:26.128
Of course, the good old
Americans help a lot of these

00:43:26.128 --> 00:43:29.920
Nazi war criminals escape to
Paraguay and places like that,

00:43:29.920 --> 00:43:33.534
in exchange for information
about communist movements and

00:43:33.534 --> 00:43:34.889
that sort of thing.
 

00:43:34.889 --> 00:43:35.760
They believed.
 

00:43:35.760 --> 00:43:36.800
They believed.
 

00:43:36.800 --> 00:43:40.646
Not everybody believed,
but that's one of the scariest

00:43:40.646 --> 00:43:44.782
things about the whole thing,
that it was sieg heil

00:43:44.782 --> 00:43:46.090
until the end.
 

00:43:46.090 --> 00:43:49.166
Again, not for everybody,
not for everybody,

00:43:49.166 --> 00:43:52.099
but for some social classes and
others.

00:43:52.099 --> 00:43:55.599
You find this in other
countries, and I'll talk a

00:43:55.599 --> 00:43:59.757
little bit about that when--I
guess I'll talk mostly about

00:43:59.757 --> 00:44:01.289
France next time.
 

00:44:07.289 --> 00:44:13.469
Hitler gives the German people
what they want.

00:44:13.469 --> 00:44:17.829
His prestige,
every time he stands down the

00:44:17.829 --> 00:44:22.429
British and the French,
every time that he pulls this

00:44:22.429 --> 00:44:25.159
off--the occupation of the
Rhineland,

00:44:25.159 --> 00:44:31.489
the absorption of the Sudeten
part of Bohemia,

00:44:31.489 --> 00:44:33.130
and then they just take over
the whole country,

00:44:33.130 --> 00:44:36.119
the Anschluss--where he's
greeted enthusiastically by the

00:44:36.119 --> 00:44:36.599
crowds.
 

00:44:36.599 --> 00:44:40.110
You can see these photos of the
adoring Viennese crowds.

00:44:40.110 --> 00:44:45.750
Where was the Vienna of calm
concerts?

00:44:45.750 --> 00:44:47.320
It became the Vienna of Wagner.
 

00:44:47.320 --> 00:44:51.349
It became the Vienna of
saluting Hitler and then going

00:44:51.349 --> 00:44:54.239
out and beating up and killing
Jews.

00:44:54.239 --> 00:45:01.199
Something like 100 Jews are
murdered in Vienna when Hitler

00:45:01.199 --> 00:45:04.130
arrives, to celebrate.
 

00:45:04.130 --> 00:45:07.690
They, too, believed.
 

00:45:07.690 --> 00:45:10.686
One of the dark secrets was the
Nazi past of the former

00:45:10.686 --> 00:45:13.849
Secretary General of the United
Nations, Kurt Waldheim.

00:45:13.849 --> 00:45:18.010
All this came out before most
of you were reading newspapers.

00:45:18.010 --> 00:45:20.539
Some of you were reading them
back then.

00:45:20.539 --> 00:45:23.000
It was about fifteen years ago,
or something like that.

00:45:23.000 --> 00:45:26.949
The people knew.
 

00:45:26.949 --> 00:45:32.460
Those are really the big points
that I wanted to make.

00:45:32.460 --> 00:45:37.625
When you were reading,
German women or German men

00:45:37.625 --> 00:45:41.422
waiting to get their hair done,
when you read a popular

00:45:41.422 --> 00:45:46.052
newspaper or popular magazine,
all of which had articles about

00:45:46.052 --> 00:45:48.014
Hitler,
and this sort of entourage and

00:45:48.014 --> 00:45:50.710
all that,
and you read a cheery headline,

00:45:50.710 --> 00:45:53.699
such as "Gas Masks for
Children Now Readied."

00:45:53.699 --> 00:45:58.670
You sort of nodded and said,
"We'll be ready for the

00:45:58.670 --> 00:46:00.179
struggle."
 

00:46:00.179 --> 00:46:05.195
What happened was Hitler's
book, Mein Kampf, became

00:46:05.195 --> 00:46:10.829
perceived of and adopted by the
majority of people in Germany.

00:46:10.829 --> 00:46:17.003
Tragically enough,
they remain with Adolf Hitler

00:46:17.003 --> 00:46:23.309
and the Nazis until the very,
very bitter end.

00:46:23.309 --> 00:46:27.753
Of course, it's important to
see the context is that in all

00:46:27.753 --> 00:46:30.795
of these places,
whether you're talking about

00:46:30.795 --> 00:46:32.715
Brussels,
whether you're talking about

00:46:32.715 --> 00:46:36.614
Amsterdam,
whether you're talking about

00:46:36.614 --> 00:46:39.867
Prague,
anyplace you're talking about

00:46:39.867 --> 00:46:42.846
in Europe,
or Oswald Mosley strutting

00:46:42.846 --> 00:46:47.159
through Hyde Park with his
little Naziling followers.

00:46:47.159 --> 00:46:50.570
Hitler was just the most
violent,

00:46:50.570 --> 00:46:54.360
the most egregious,
the most horrible,

00:46:54.360 --> 00:46:57.925
the most tragic example of what
was a general phenomenon

00:46:57.925 --> 00:47:02.842
throughout the entire period,
at different degrees of success

00:47:02.842 --> 00:47:05.409
during the 1920s and 1930s.
 

00:47:05.409 --> 00:47:11.409
The war that began in 1914
basically does not end,

00:47:11.409 --> 00:47:19.630
at least in Europe,
until the defeat finally of

00:47:19.630 --> 00:47:23.889
Germany,
and the death of Adolf Hitler,

00:47:23.889 --> 00:47:25.780
still at a relatively young
age,

00:47:25.780 --> 00:47:27.446
in the bunker in Berlin.
 

